Rephrase the text using other words: To sum up, we’ve listed the most important advantages of the corpus analysis:
-	The corpus contains examples from real language practice, and not invented by the author to illustrate a particular phenomenon, thus eliminating doubt about the authenticity of the discussed samples of a particular linguistic phenomenon;
-	The corpus offers data on the linguistic variability of a unit depending on the type of discourse, which suggests the possibility of selective result orientation for specialists in specific fields of activity;
-	The corpus data indicate the frequency of use of the unit, which allows sorting samples depending on the level of language training of students;
-	The corpus represents the context of the use of the unit, that is, the opportunity to evaluate it from the perspective of a discursive modality;
-	The corpus contains lexico-grammatical models (collocations), that is, the words most used in the desired construction and their characteristic combinations, and thus eliminates the lacuna existing in the minds of language learners between vocabulary and grammar.
